// ── Phase 05.1 Gap D: NN↔NB dialect-mix FLAG cases ──
// Mirror of fixtures/nb/typo.jsonl. An NN document with NB-only tokens
// flags via the new nb-dialect-mix rule (priority 35). Coexistence model:
// non-curated sister-valid tokens (tokens in NN's sisterValidWords but
// missing from curated NB_TO_NN) are silently tolerated by the Phase 4
// sisterValidWords guard still present in typo-curated / typo-fuzzy.
//
// Reality observed at executor run: the 5 Phase 4 dialect tokens (jeg,
// ikke, bare, noen, hjem) are all in NN's validWords via the vocab-seam
// translation-entry path — NN entries with translation 'jeg' / 'ikke' /
// etc. seed those strings into NN validWords. So dialect-mix doesn't
// fire on them (the guard is "sister-valid AND NOT current-valid"). The
// Phase 4 fixtures therefore stay expected:[] — the document-side data
// considers these words valid NN (empirically, via translation entries).
// New cases below test tokens that ARE genuinely NB-only per the data.
//
// Runner contract: strict equality on (rule_id, start, end, fix === suggestion).
{"id":"nn-typo-dialect-jeg-001","text":"Eg såg at jeg sto der i går","expected":[],"must_not_flag":[]}
